01:12:25,587 --> 01:12:29,759
But we just got
to keep going, right?

1207
01:12:29,792 --> 01:12:34,030
And we got to remember
all of those who are with us.

1208
01:12:35,698 --> 01:12:37,967
And the last thing grandpa
would have wanted

1209
01:12:38,000 --> 01:12:42,537
was for us to be sad
or feel guilty.

1210
01:12:44,206 --> 01:12:47,910
He'd want us to live
our lives to the fullest.

1211
01:12:48,911 --> 01:12:49,677
Right?

1212
01:12:52,048 --> 01:12:58,020
So you sing
and you barrel race...

1213
01:13:00,022 --> 01:13:01,656
and fall in love...

1214
01:13:04,393 --> 01:13:06,262
and make your grandpa proud...

1215
01:13:08,197 --> 01:13:10,199
[sobbing]

1216
01:13:10,232 --> 01:13:14,303
...because he is watching
over all of us.

1217
01:13:14,336 --> 01:13:15,137
Okay?

1218
01:13:25,014 --> 01:13:29,318
Hey, Maddie, just checking in.

1219
01:13:29,351 --> 01:13:31,854
Call me back
when you get a chance.

1220
01:13:31,887 --> 01:13:33,055
All right, bye.

1221
01:13:34,757 --> 01:13:36,292
I wonder where she is?

1222
01:13:36,325 --> 01:13:38,194
- I don't know.
- [mobile chimes]

1223
01:13:41,864 --> 01:13:44,066
Can you believe Rufus
just turned 18 today?

1224
01:13:44,100 --> 01:13:47,136
- He said he was 19.
- I thought he was 12.

1225
01:13:47,169 --> 01:13:49,205
[birds chirping]

1226
01:13:51,440 --> 01:13:53,809
Which means he was 17 last week.

1227
01:13:53,843 --> 01:13:55,010
[door opens]

1228
01:13:56,011 --> 01:13:59,181
Grandma, can you give
us a ride somewhere?

1229
01:13:59,215 --> 01:14:01,383
Mr. Daniels is just pulling up.
Come on, we'll take you.

1230
01:14:01,417 --> 01:14:02,617
[car approaches]

1231
01:14:03,886 --> 01:14:06,021
Mr. Daniels,
can we give the girls a ride?

1232
01:14:06,055 --> 01:14:07,389
Sure, ladies. Come on.

1233
01:14:08,891 --> 01:14:11,260
Yeah, yeah. Listen, I need you to
meet us at that horse betting place.

1234
01:14:11,293 --> 01:14:13,863
Can you be there in ten minutes?
Rufus.

1235
01:14:13,896 --> 01:14:15,865
Rufus, just come, okay?

1236
01:14:15,898 --> 01:14:17,199
Okay, see you there.

1237
01:14:23,339 --> 01:14:26,008
Hailey, I'm telling you,
there's no way to get the money back.

1238
01:14:26,041 --> 01:14:29,211
- Will you at least help me try?
- [people cheering on TV]

1239
01:14:29,245 --> 01:14:30,980
Now, I'll do whatever I can.

1240
01:14:32,114 --> 01:14:34,250
Okay, who did you place
your bets with?

1241
01:14:34,283 --> 01:14:36,719
The guy at the end there,
George.

1242
01:14:38,287 --> 01:14:39,788
[Hailey] All right. Let's go.

1243
01:14:43,792 --> 01:14:46,095
Um, hi, George.

1244
01:14:46,128 --> 01:14:48,998
- You know Rufus, right?
- Hi, George.

1245
01:14:49,031 --> 01:14:50,766
Yeah. Hey, Rufus.

1246
01:14:50,799 --> 01:14:53,869
Are you sure you want
to try this again? [chuckles]

1247
01:14:53,903 --> 01:14:58,374
Well, you see, George,
the $50,000 that Rufus lost last week

1248
01:14:58,407 --> 01:15:00,843
also belonged to me,
so we're here to get it back.

1249
01:15:00,876 --> 01:15:03,312
Yeah, well,
that ain't gonna happen.

1250
01:15:03,345 --> 01:15:05,481
All bets are final.

1251
01:15:05,514 --> 01:15:07,683
It ain't my problem
he lost your money, lady.

1252
01:15:08,951 --> 01:15:11,387
Well, you see,
it actually is your problem

1253
01:15:11,420 --> 01:15:15,424
because Rufus was a minor when you took
all those bets from him and that's illegal.

1254
01:15:15,457 --> 01:15:17,159
Whoa... hey!

1255
01:15:17,193 --> 01:15:19,495
- I didn't know he's a minor.
- Yes, you did.

1256
01:15:19,528 --> 01:15:22,164
You were charging 20 percent for
the risk that you were taking.

1257
01:15:22,198 --> 01:15:25,201
Okay, look. So even if I did,
and I ain't saying I did...

1258
01:15:26,302 --> 01:15:28,337
you got no proof
he was ever even here.

1259
01:15:28,370 --> 01:15:30,472
I don't know. I mean, come on.

1260
01:15:30,506 --> 01:15:34,443
With the face like this, I don't think
people around here could forget it.

1261
01:15:34,476 --> 01:15:35,711
Thanks.

1262
01:15:35,744 --> 01:15:40,182
And taking a $50,000 bet from
a minor sounds pretty bad to me.

1263
01:15:40,216 --> 01:15:42,184
It was actually a $40,000 bet.

1264
01:15:42,218 --> 01:15:44,386
He took the 10,000
for himself off top.

1265
01:15:44,420 --> 01:15:46,355
Well, it's getting
worse and worse.

1266
01:15:46,388 --> 01:15:50,192
Oh, actually, it's a criminal
offense with a pretty stiff penalty.

1267
01:15:50,226 --> 01:15:51,460
You know, all right,
all right, all right.

1268
01:15:51,493 --> 01:15:53,796
I'll give you
the lousy ten grand.

1269
01:15:53,829 --> 01:15:55,931
You can bet
on any horse you like.

1270
01:15:55,965 --> 01:15:57,433
The last race is in ten minutes,

1271
01:15:57,466 --> 01:15:59,835
so you ain't got a whole lot
of time, Sister.

1272
01:16:02,371 --> 01:16:03,906
Okay. We'll do it.

1273
01:16:05,908 --> 01:16:08,410
Hailey, are you sure you want
to let Rufus bet that money?

1274
01:16:08,444 --> 01:16:10,913
He doesn't have a very
good track record.

1275
01:16:10,946 --> 01:16:14,183
- No pun intended.
- What else can we do?

1276
01:16:14,216 --> 01:16:16,185
$10,000 isn't gonna help dad.

1277
01:16:18,053 --> 01:16:22,057
- Just have to pray.
- Okay.

1278
01:16:22,091 --> 01:16:24,893
Looks like there's a lot of
praying going on around here.

1279
01:16:24,927 --> 01:16:28,063
- [alarm blares]
- [indistinct announcement]

1280
01:16:28,097 --> 01:16:29,098
What about For The Win?

1281
01:16:30,199 --> 01:16:33,135
No, no, no, no, no.
For The Win is only two to one.

1282
01:16:33,168 --> 01:16:34,503
There are three horses
that are five to one,

1283
01:16:34,536 --> 01:16:36,405
your best bet is going
to be Silent Speed.

1284
01:16:36,438 --> 01:16:39,508
The best time
last three races, good jockey.

1285
01:16:39,541 --> 01:16:42,911
- Are you sure?
- I'm sure, Hailey.

1286
01:16:42,945 --> 01:16:44,013
I can feel it in my bones.

1287
01:16:45,848 --> 01:16:49,084
Normally, I would not condone
betting on a horse race.

1288
01:16:50,085 --> 01:16:51,954
But these are not normal times.

1289
01:16:54,957 --> 01:16:55,958
Let's do it.

1290
01:16:57,593 --> 01:16:59,261
[announcer] <i>And they're off. This is
the tenth and last race of the day.</i>

1291
01:16:59,295 --> 01:17:00,162
Come on, Silent Speed.

1292
01:17:02,464 --> 01:17:06,435
- <i>Yeah, come on, Silent speed.</i>
- [Hailey] Go, Silent Speed.

1293
01:17:06,468 --> 01:17:07,469
Come on, come on!

1294
01:17:09,938 --> 01:17:13,575
Get the lightening out,
Silent Speed. Come on!

1295
01:17:13,609 --> 01:17:14,810
Come on, come on.

1296
01:17:14,843 --> 01:17:16,545
[announcer] <i>...and Peter Piper
second and third.</i>

1297
01:17:16,578 --> 01:17:19,481
- <i>For The Win making his move on the inside.</i>
- Come on. Come on.

1298
01:17:19,515 --> 01:17:22,851
[announcer] <i>Silent Speed faltering and
For The Win takes the lead by a nose.</i>

1299
01:17:22,885 --> 01:17:25,254
- <i>Silent Speed tries to make a move on the outside...</i>
- [Brook] Come on, Silent Speed.

1300
01:17:25,287 --> 01:17:27,589
[announcer] <i>...but Peter Piper
maintains lead for third.</i>

1301
01:17:27,623 --> 01:17:29,058
<i>At the finish,</i>

1302
01:17:29,091 --> 01:17:32,861
<i>it's For The Win at first place
followed by Silent Speed in second</i>

1303
01:17:32,895 --> 01:17:34,863
<i>and Peter Piper shows for third.</i>

1304
01:17:36,532 --> 01:17:38,100
Hailey, I'm so sorry.

1305
01:17:39,335 --> 01:17:40,502
I'm so sorry.

1306
01:17:47,009 --> 01:17:48,177
I know. We'll figure it out.

1307
01:17:52,348 --> 01:17:55,384
[announcer] <i>Ladies and gentlemen,
an update from today's final race.</i>

1308
01:17:55,417 --> 01:17:58,187
<i>For The Win
has been disqualified</i>

1309
01:17:58,220 --> 01:18:01,156
<i>and Silent Speed
moves up to first.</i>

1310
01:18:01,190 --> 01:18:02,391
<i>Peter Piper goes into second...</i>

1311
01:18:02,424 --> 01:18:04,893
- No way!
- Are you kidding me?

1312
01:18:04,927 --> 01:18:07,663
- Yes! Yeah!
- [all cheering]

1313
01:18:07,697 --> 01:18:10,132
- Yes!
- We did it.

1314
01:18:11,033 --> 01:18:12,034
We got them!

1315
01:18:13,135 --> 01:18:14,536
[laughing] That's amazing.

1316
01:18:15,170 --> 01:18:17,373
[Erin] Oh, my goodness!
Can y'all believe that?

1317
01:18:17,406 --> 01:18:19,908
- Oh, I almost had a heart attack.
- [Hailey laughing]

1318
01:18:19,942 --> 01:18:21,677
You really love money,
don't you?

1319
01:18:21,711 --> 01:18:24,146
- What's not to like about 50K?
- All right.

1320
01:18:24,179 --> 01:18:28,350
Um... Okay. Hey, Maddie, uh,

1321
01:18:28,384 --> 01:18:30,185
just trying to get
a hold of you again.

1322
01:18:30,219 --> 01:18:31,320
Got some really great news,

1323
01:18:31,353 --> 01:18:34,056
so I don't know, call me back
when you get a chance.

1324
01:18:34,691 --> 01:18:36,191
All right. Bye.

1325
01:18:36,225 --> 01:18:38,560
[ambulance siren wailing]

1326
01:18:49,438 --> 01:18:51,640
We need to follow that ambulance.
Grandma! Mr. Daniels!

1327
01:19:00,048 --> 01:19:01,083
[Hailey] What happened?

1328
01:19:01,116 --> 01:19:03,185
We found her unresponsive
on her kitchen floor.

1329
01:19:10,993 --> 01:19:12,494
Are any of you related
to Maddie?

1330
01:19:12,528 --> 01:19:14,563
Uh, we're her close friends.

1331
01:19:14,596 --> 01:19:16,432
I don't think
she has any family.

1332
01:19:16,465 --> 01:19:17,466
How is she?

1333
01:19:18,701 --> 01:19:22,237
She's stable, but her lupus
is more serious than we thought.

1334
01:19:22,271 --> 01:19:25,674
I feel we need to move on to the
next step which is immunotherapy.

1335
01:19:25,708 --> 01:19:27,209
Uh, when can you start that?

1336
01:19:27,242 --> 01:19:29,611
Well, the treatment
is very expensive

1337
01:19:29,645 --> 01:19:31,681
and she doesn't have
health insurance.

1338
01:19:31,714 --> 01:19:33,382
So we can't do it at this time.

1339
01:19:34,383 --> 01:19:39,455
Um, what will happen to her
if you can't do the treatment?

1340
01:19:41,490 --> 01:19:43,992
Her condition
will worsen over time

1341
01:19:44,026 --> 01:19:46,195
and her episodes
will become more severe.

1342
01:19:49,164 --> 01:19:51,233
I wish I had better
news for you.

1343
01:19:51,266 --> 01:19:52,434
One of you can go see her now.

1344
01:19:54,069 --> 01:19:55,738
- Go ahead, honey.
- Okay.

1345
01:20:00,375 --> 01:20:02,110
[indistinct chatter]

1346
01:20:02,144 --> 01:20:03,312
- Hey.
- Hey.

1347
01:20:06,482 --> 01:20:07,483
Hey.

1348
01:20:09,418 --> 01:20:12,187
I have a flair
for the dramatic, don't I?

1349
01:20:12,221 --> 01:20:14,089
Some people will do
anything for attention.

1350
01:20:14,122 --> 01:20:15,390
[both chuckling]

1351
01:20:15,424 --> 01:20:18,126
- That's me, drama queen.
- Mm-hmm.

1352
01:20:20,162 --> 01:20:21,731
How do you feel?

1353
01:20:21,764 --> 01:20:22,765
Okay.

1354
01:20:24,299 --> 01:20:27,770
Doctor says I need some
expensive new drug,

1355
01:20:27,804 --> 01:20:29,338
but I told her...

1356
01:20:31,206 --> 01:20:32,641
I'm a waitress, so...

1357
01:20:34,476 --> 01:20:36,478
You're gonna be okay, Maddie.

1358
01:20:36,512 --> 01:20:38,380
That's nice of you
to say that...

1359
01:20:39,749 --> 01:20:42,117
but I've been dealing
with this my whole life and...

1360
01:20:43,418 --> 01:20:45,587
it was bound to catch up
with me one of these days.

1361
01:20:50,727 --> 01:20:52,427
I don't want you to lose hope.

1362
01:20:53,662 --> 01:20:55,531
Okay, Maddie.

1363
01:20:55,564 --> 01:20:57,633
It looks like I need
to get some blood.

1364
01:20:57,666 --> 01:20:59,268
Yippie.

1365
01:20:59,301 --> 01:21:02,604
And this is where I exit.
Extreme needle phobia.

1366
01:21:02,638 --> 01:21:04,339
- Lightweight.
- Um...

1367
01:21:04,373 --> 01:21:06,508
We'll all be in the waiting
room if you need us.

1368
01:21:06,542 --> 01:21:07,543
Okay.

1369
01:21:08,878 --> 01:21:11,513
[somber music playing]

1370
01:21:11,547 --> 01:21:13,382
She's resting.

1371
01:21:13,415 --> 01:21:15,785
Thank you all so much
for being here.

1372
01:21:15,818 --> 01:21:17,185
Of course, we'd be here.

1373
01:21:39,742 --> 01:21:41,510
Are y'all thinking
what I'm thinking?

1374
01:21:42,745 --> 01:21:44,814
I think we are.

1375
01:21:44,847 --> 01:21:46,849
Do you mean use this
money for Maddie?

1376
01:21:53,522 --> 01:21:55,324
What about daddy?

1377
01:21:55,357 --> 01:21:57,593
Oh, honey, he'll understand.

1378
01:21:57,626 --> 01:21:59,528
And he'll be all right.

1379
01:21:59,561 --> 01:22:04,132
And I'll just unretire again
and we'll raise some more money.

1380
01:22:04,166 --> 01:22:07,837
Y'all, that's too much
to ask of you.

1381
01:22:07,870 --> 01:22:09,772
It's the right thing
to do, Collin.

1382
01:22:11,173 --> 01:22:13,710
That money right there was
meant for Maddie's treatment.

1383
01:22:15,577 --> 01:22:18,915
You know, Erin, uh, everyone,
I didn't want to overstep,

1384
01:22:18,948 --> 01:22:23,185
but, um, before I retired
in my early career,

1385
01:22:23,218 --> 01:22:25,621
I was a pretty
successful attorney.

1386
01:22:26,823 --> 01:22:29,424
- You were?
- Among other things.

1387
01:22:29,458 --> 01:22:34,764
So I'd be happy to unretire
and take your son's case.

1388
01:22:34,797 --> 01:22:36,465
Pro bono, of course.

1389
01:22:37,599 --> 01:22:40,535
- What's pro bono?
- Means for free.

1390
01:22:40,569 --> 01:22:44,606
Ah. Wow! Thank you.

1391
01:22:44,640 --> 01:22:47,910
- Yeah, thank you, Mr. Daniels.
- You're welcome.

1392
01:22:47,944 --> 01:22:49,344
And in order to better
serve your son,

1393
01:22:49,378 --> 01:22:53,482
first thing I'd do is weigh the jury
and, uh, request a bench trial.

1394
01:22:55,250 --> 01:22:57,920
- Well, you sound like you know what you're talking about.
- [chuckles]

1395
01:23:00,589 --> 01:23:02,491
We gratefully accept.

1396
01:23:03,325 --> 01:23:04,326
It would be my pleasure.

1397
01:23:09,799 --> 01:23:11,466
It looks like
you got some visitors.

1398
01:23:12,467 --> 01:23:13,635
Thank you.

1399
01:23:13,669 --> 01:23:16,571
- Hey, guys.
- Hey.

1400
01:23:16,605 --> 01:23:18,407
- Thank you. - Thank you.
- Yeah. Of course.

1401
01:23:18,440 --> 01:23:23,445
Um, Maddie, we have something
important to tell you.

1402
01:23:23,478 --> 01:23:26,916
We just want you to know
that we have all agreed on this.

1403
01:23:26,949 --> 01:23:27,950
Even Rufus.

1404
01:23:29,052 --> 01:23:31,486
We've decided to use the money
from the fundraiser

1405
01:23:31,520 --> 01:23:33,188
to help pay
for your treatment.

1406
01:23:34,423 --> 01:23:37,794
No, you guys.

1407
01:23:37,827 --> 01:23:39,696
- It's what we're gonna do.
- Yeah.

1408
01:23:39,729 --> 01:23:43,766
Oh, thank you so much.
Oh, my gosh!

1409
01:23:43,800 --> 01:23:46,268
- Of course.
- Thank you.

1410
01:23:46,301 --> 01:23:47,536
Yeah. You're gonna be okay.

1411
01:23:49,304 --> 01:23:52,474
When you agreed to drive
the truck for Mr. Robins,

1412
01:23:52,507 --> 01:23:54,977
did you know the truck
was full of TVs?

1413
01:23:55,011 --> 01:23:56,445
Yes, Sir. I did.

1414
01:23:56,478 --> 01:23:59,448
And, uh, did you know these
TVs were stolen?

1415
01:23:59,481 --> 01:24:02,785
No, Sir. I thought I was doing
a favor for a friend.

1416
01:24:02,819 --> 01:24:06,689
Even though you knew this friend
had a history of criminal activity?

1417
01:24:06,723 --> 01:24:10,727
Yes, Sir. I...
I believe people can change.

1418
01:24:10,760 --> 01:24:12,527
He assured me that he had.

1419
01:24:12,561 --> 01:24:15,464
Well, exactly how long have you
and Mr. Robins been friends?

1420
01:24:15,497 --> 01:24:18,801
My whole life. Uh, we went
to grammar school together.

1421
01:24:18,835 --> 01:24:22,337
He got me my first real job.
He was a good friend to me.

1422
01:24:22,370 --> 01:24:27,744
I would ask the defense Exhibit 1 be
entered into the record for evidence.

1423
01:24:27,777 --> 01:24:32,982
It's a copy of an email from Mr. Mays to
Mr. Bill Robins from one month before.

1424
01:24:33,015 --> 01:24:35,317
I need Mr. Mays
to read a portion of it.

1425
01:24:37,419 --> 01:24:40,388
- Response?
- No objections.

1426
01:24:40,422 --> 01:24:41,423
Admitted.

1427
01:24:43,760 --> 01:24:47,562
Mr. Mays, would you please
read the last two lines?

1428
01:24:47,596 --> 01:24:51,366
"I know times have been rough
for you the past few years, Bill,

1429
01:24:51,399 --> 01:24:54,036
"but I want you to know
that I'm here for you

1430
01:24:54,070 --> 01:24:57,740
"and if there's anything I can
help you with, you can call me.

1431
01:24:57,774 --> 01:24:59,208
"You've always been
a good friend of me..."

1432
01:24:59,242 --> 01:25:03,545
Your Honor, Mr. Mays is a hard-working
citizen with no prior records.

1433
01:25:03,578 --> 01:25:05,580
I do see a breaking
and entering.

1434
01:25:05,614 --> 01:25:09,584
Oh, that was when he was a minor
and it was taken off his record.

1435
01:25:09,618 --> 01:25:10,853
Yes, I see that.

1436
01:25:10,887 --> 01:25:14,023
He's had the same job for ten
years with the same employer.

1437
01:25:14,056 --> 01:25:16,826
He's also a family man
